## Gherkin patterns for complex form interactions

### Accordion / collapse patterns

```gherkin
# DON'T write this (codegen style — tests the implementation):
When I check the "Residential" checkbox
Then the "Residential" checkbox should be checked

# DO write this (BDD style — tests the behaviour):
When I indicate I am a residential customer
Then I should see the residential address form
And the business details section should not be visible
```

```ts
// Step implementation:
When('I indicate I am a residential customer', async function(this: PwCraftWorld) {
  const smart = new SmartWaitHelper(this.page);
  await smart.forActionOutcome(
    () => this.action.click(this.find.checkboxByLabel('Residential')),
    this.find.byTestId('residential-form'),
    { timeout: 10_000 }
  );
});
```

### Multi-step form wizard

```gherkin
Scenario: Complete address form
  Given I am on the checkout page
  When I fill in the form:
    | Full name   | Jane Doe          |
    | Street      | 123 Main St       |
    | City        | London            |
  And I indicate delivery is to a different address
  Then the delivery address form should be visible
  When I fill in the delivery form:
    | Full name   | John Doe          |
    | Street      | 456 Other Road    |
```

